<h1 id="here-is-the-requirements-for-the-project-">Here is the requirements for the project.</h1>
<p>Description: Create a personal website using html5 and CSS that is hosted on GitHub and provides information about you. This project is similar to the Midterm Project but instead of creating a website using markdown, you will be using html5 and CSS to create your website. You can use the same content from the midterm project or create new content. The choice is yours.</p>
<p>Your website will ultimately be hosted on GitHub Pages Links to an external site.but you should develop and test your site on your computer and when it is done you can push the site to your GitHub repository.</p>
<p>Purpose: This project provides experience working with html5, CSS, Git/GitHub, and IT-related concepts and knowledge.</p>
<p>Requirements:</p>
<p>This project is to be managed in a public GitHub repository. Submit the Clone with HTTPS URL for the repository that contains the files to your site.  The URL is available when you click on the green Code button on a repository web page. You will also submit the URL to the GitHub pages site you create. </p>
